and the man does not die but takes to his bed,

21:19

then if the man rises again and walks outdoors with his staff,

he who struck him shall be clear; only he shall pay for the loss of his time,

and shall have him thoroughly healed.

21:20

When a man strikes his slave, male or female, with a rod

and the slave dies under his hand, he shall be avenged.

21:21

But if the slave survives a day or two, he is not to be avenged,

for the slave is his money.

21:22

When men strive together and hit a pregnant woman, so that her children come out,

but there is no harm, the one who hit her shall surely be fined,

